{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b266e460-283e-4168-b0af-337e051867d2","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — re-run tests automatically on file save (hot reload)\n- **`--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~...\"`** — only run tests whose name contains that string\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so you don't need the full namespace. If the test name is unique, you can also shorten it:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"DisplayName~NegativeAmount\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2eb756dc-8077-4693-a527-63148371f01c","outputTokens":161,"requestId":"67D0:1FC0A0:17F31CC:1B04AE0:69FD427C"},"id":"a7cd9369-10cf-4f0d-a490-9b92efc380ef","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:55:14.567Z","parentId":"8f944e48-e538-403f-a493-9cb574305372"}
